  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is the best answer because the graph shows that Montr&eacute;al had the largest population in 1891 among the four cities represented. According to the data points in the graph for the year 1891, Montr&eacute;al&rsquo;s population was approximately 220,000, which is greater than the respective populations of Toronto (approximately 180,000), Qu&eacute;bec City (approximately 60,000), and Halifax (approximately 40,000).</p><p>Choice A is incorrect because Toronto&rsquo;s population in 1891 was approximately 180,000, which is the second largest among the four cities shown but still clearly smaller than Montr&eacute;al&rsquo;s population of approximately 220,000. Choice C is incorrect because Qu&eacute;bec City had a population of approximately 60,000 in 1891, making it only the third largest of the four cities shown. Choice D is incorrect because Halifax had a population of approximately 40,000 people in 1891. Of the four cities shown in the graph, Halifax has the smallest population, not the largest.</p>",
