<line x1=\"192.97656297683716\" y1=\"178\" x2=\"261.7859377861023\" y2=\"127.33333333333331\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2.4\" stroke-dasharray=\"9 6\" marker-end=\"url(#marker1)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker1)\"/><line x1=\"192.97656297683716\" y1=\"230.66666666666666\" x2=\"261.7859377861023\" y2=\"230\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"3\" stroke-dasharray=\"1.1 6\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" marker-end=\"url(#marker2)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker2)\"/><line x1=\"192.97656297683716\" y1=\"214.66666666666666\" x2=\"261.7859377861023\" y2=\"151.33333333333331\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"3.5\" marker-end=\"url(#marker3)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker3)\"/><line x1=\"261.7859377861023\" y1=\"246\" x2=\"330.59531259536743\" y2=\"244.66666666666666\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2.4\" marker-end=\"url(#marker0)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker0)\"/><line x1=\"261.7859377861023\" y1=\"127.33333333333331\" x2=\"330.59531259536743\" y2=\"93.33333333333334\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2.4\" stroke-dasharray=\"9 6\" marker-end=\"url(#marker1)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker1)\"/><line x1=\"261.7859377861023\" y1=\"230\" x2=\"330.59531259536743\" y2=\"226\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"3\" stroke-dasharray=\"1.1 6\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" marker-end=\"url(#marker2)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker2)\"/><line x1=\"261.7859377861023\" y1=\"151.33333333333331\" x2=\"330.59531259536743\" y2=\"133.33333333333331\" stroke=\"#999\" stroke-width=\"3.5\" marker-end=\"url(#marker3)\" marker-start=\"url(#marker3)\"/></g></svg></figure><div class=\"sr-only\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Long description for line graph titled Census Data for Four Canadian Cities, 1871\u20131901\"><ul>\n<li>The following 4 lines are shown:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>Halifax</li>\n<li>Montr&eacute;al</li>\n<li>Qu&eacute;bec City</li>\n<li>Toronto</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Halifax line:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>Begins at 1871, 30 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1881, 36 thousand&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1891, 39 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1901, 41 thousand</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Montr&eacute;al line:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>Begins at 1871, 107 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1881, 141 thousand&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rises sharply to 1891, 217 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises sharply to 1901, 268 thousand</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Qu&eacute;bec City line:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>Begins at 1871, 60 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1881, 62 thousand&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1891, 63 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1901, 69 thousand</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The Toronto line:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>Begins at 1871, 56 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1881, 86 thousand&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rises sharply to 1891, 181 thousand</li>\n<li>Rises gradually to 1901, 208 thousand</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div>\n<p>The first national census in Canada was conducted in <span data-ssml-say-as=\"date\">1871</span>. The graph shows the population sizes of some of the largest Canadian cities from each of the first four national censuses, which occurred every ten years.</p>"
